channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Team DeSantis Dunks on NY Timesâ€”Where's Your Correction, Gray Lady?
Biden camp jabs at Trump's 'failed' business record as former president looks to sway nation's top CEOs
item.description: The Biden campaign is attacking Trump over his business record, calling him a "fraud," and "crook" ahead of his appearance at a Business Roundtable event with top CEOs.

item.title: Reuters Poll: Trump Flips Race to 2-Point Lead After Verdict
item.description: Donald Trump, the Republican challenger in the U.S. presidential contest, opened up a marginal 2 percentage point lead over President Joe Biden this week in the race to win the November election, as voters weigh the recent criminal convictions.

item.title: Rep. Burchett Demands Investigation of Hunter Intel Letter, Then Destroys Dem 'Operative' in Laugh of Day
Biden to sign 10-year security agreement with Ukraine at G-7 summit
item.description: President Biden and Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy will sign an agreement assuring U.S. military support for Ukraine for another 10 years on Thursday.

item.title: G7 Summit Opens With Deal to Use Russian Assets for Ukraine
item.description: A Group of Seven summit is opening Thursday with agreement on a U.S. proposal to back a $50 billion loan to Ukraine using frozen Russian assets as collateral, giving Kyiv a strong show of support even as Europe's political chessboard shifts to the right.Diplomats confirmed...

item.title: WATCH: Protesters Storm the Field at Congressional Baseball Game, Before Getting Tackled, Dragged Away
Potential candidates for Supreme Court under a second Donald Trump term
item.description: Former President Donald Trump is expected to release a list of options that he would use to select as candidates for judicial nominees if he is elected president.

item.title: Jewish Leaders: Reinstate New York Mask Ban
item.description: Confronting a sharp rise in antisemitic incidents, several Jewish community leaders in New York City are advocating for the revival of an anti-mask law to prevent protesters from concealing their identities during hate-fueled demonstrations, the New York Post reported.

item.title: Goldie Hawn Says She Lives in Fear After Home Break-Ins - California's Crime Also Reaching Celebrities
House committee subpoenas 15 Biden Cabinet secretaries to hand over documents on voter mobilization 'scheme'
item.description: A House committee is issuing over a dozen subpoenas to Biden's Cabinet over concerns with Biden's March 2021 executive order related to voting and how the agencies will carry it out.

item.title: AG Garland: GOP Uses Contempt Vote as Political Weapon
item.description: Attorney General Merrick Garland said Wednesday the vote to hold him in contempt of Congress by House Republicans was being used as a "partisan weapon."

item.title: Hillary Clinton Endorses AGAINST Embattled Squad Member Jamaal Bowman, but Will Anyone Care?
Another House member calls on New York Democratic Gov. Hochul to pardon Trump: 'Your solemn duty'
item.description: Rep. Claudia Tenney, R-N.Y., urged New York Gov. Kathy Hochul to pardon former President Trump and remove Manhattan District Attorney Alvin Bragg after Trump's hush money trial.

item.title: Trump, Biden Hold Dueling London Fundraisers
item.description: Supporters of President Joe Biden and former President Donald Trump held simultaneous fundraisers in Great Britain on Wednesday evening, Financial Times reported.
